article.headline: Wis.-Milwaukee 57, Cleveland St. 56 OT
article.story: MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Avery Smith scored 17 points, Allan Hanson 13 and Kevin Massiah 10 to help Wisconsin-Milwaukee defeat Cleveland State 57-56 in overtime in a Horizon League game Monday night. The Panthers (8-16, 5-6) snapped a two-game losing streak and beat the Vikings for the 10th straight game. The Vikings (8-15, 2-8) lost for the sixth time in their last eight games. Bahaadar Russell scored 20 points and J'Nathan Bullock 12 to lead Cleveland State. Hanson hit a 3-pointer 15 seconds into the overtime period for a 50-47 Milwaukee advantage, and the Panthers pulled ahead before Bullock scored with 1:04 left to make it 57-56. Cleveland State's Raheem Moss missed an attempt at a game-winning shot at the buzzer. Smith hit two free throws with 2:32 remaining in regulation to put the Panthers ahead 47-45, but Victor Morris, fouled by Hanson on a drive, tied it at 47-47 by making two free throws with 30 seconds left to force the overtime. The Panthers led 23-18 at the half after the missed 15 of their first 17 shots. Cleveland State outscored Milwaukee 8-3 to open the second half and tie the game at 26-26 on a basket by Patrick Tatham, but Paige Paulsen, Massiah and Hanson scored consecutive baskets to put the Panthers ahead 32-26.
